The paper deals with the diffusion of products in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves algorithmic questions and computational complexity, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses graph theory to analyze the properties of social networks, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
